The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Bangla shock for England
                                                                                                                       7                                        Bangla shock for England
          
	Bristol: Bangladesh defeated England by five runs in the second one-day International, here on Saturday. Chasing Bangladeshs score of 236 for seven, the hosts were all out for 231 in 49.3 overs.         
	Jonathan Trott, who fought hard for his 94 (130 balls, 8x4), was the last man to be dismissed. Ian Bell who has fractured his foot remained not out at the non-strikers end. Mashrafe Mortaza was adjudged the Man of the Match for scoring a quickfire 22 and taking two wickets.         
	Earlier, opener Imrul Kayes (76) scored his fourth half-century after England captain Andrew Strauss opted to field after winning the toss. Bangladesh lost key wickets at the County Ground after reaching 106 for two in 21 overs.           (AGENCIES)                                                                                                                 
